description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic Clinical Psychologist with experience of working with young people with Learning Disabilities and Autism to join our Intensive Home Treatment Teams in CAMHS North Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Intensive Home Treatment Team (IHTT) in CAMHS is a successful multi-disciplinary team that supports young people with mental health problems to stay out of in-patient care. Over the last few years there has been a lot of focus on ASD and the additional support required to keep young people in the community. The post holder will work closely with the Team Lead for IHTT offering specialist advice and consultations about the young people with ASD and/or learning disabilities. They will also carry out assessments, formulations and interventions. In addition to this they will have the opportunity to contribute to relevant projects and training programmes. The post holder will have their work managed and supervised by the Team Lead and Consultant Clinical Psychologist for LD CAMHS / CDC Psychology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be a qualified Clinical Psychologist, registered with HCPC and:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have significant experience in working with young people with learning disabilities and / or Autism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally have PBS training or experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have proven excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a strong commitment to multi-disciplinary working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based within CAMHS at The Den, Chesterfield Royal Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post will require a Disclosure and Barring Service check.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Penny Tunnicliffe - Clinical Psychologist CDC Psychology or Lucy Broom Principal Clinical Psychologist for LD CAMHS on (01246) 514412.&lt;/p&gt;
